Panel 8 involved in edges (panel_a=1 panel_b=8) and (panel_a=7 panel_b=8).
With synthetic planes: 0 insertions on both (hip apex solver keeps vertices close to original).
With real DSM planes: apex moved significantly -> spurious insertions via mutation chain -> 65.9% failure.

RuntimeError from real run (as reported in plan):
  panel 8: make_valid produced MultiPolygon with largest piece ratio 0.659 < 0.95 -- too much geometry lost

--- POST-FIX ---

Fix applied: added `source_snapshot` dict in densify_edges() that captures all
polygon vertices BEFORE the edge iteration loop. Source vertex lookups now read
from `source_snapshot[source_pid]` instead of `out[source_pid]`, breaking the
mutation chain that caused spurious vertex accumulation on multi-neighbor panels.

Post-fix verification:
- Panel 8 vertex count: 5 before densify, 5 after (0 growth)
- All 12 panels survive densify_edges without error
- All multi-neighbor panels show <= 1 vertex growth (no mutation chain)
- 49/49 tests pass (3 existing densify + 3 new regression + 43 other)

The fix is narrow (D-06): only changed how source polygons are looked up.
API signature unchanged (D-07). No fallback path added (D-08).
